Tanner Ainge, chairman of the Utah County Commission, told POLITICO that Americans are suffering on both the health and economic fronts.
Cities such as Los Angeles and Philadelphia have seen spikes in calls to suicide hotlines.
A mental health clinic in L.A. reported fielding more than 1,800 coronavirus calls in March, compared with only 20 in February.
“The coronavirus pandemic is a challenge for all of us, but we’ll make it through this,” she wrote.
The sheriff’s office responded to 31 domestic violence calls in March but about 200 from March 15 to Tuesday.